[CHANGE LOG]
timestamp: 2026-05-01T11:00:00Z
change_type: architecture
scope: project setup
description: Decided to use FastAPI for the backend with SQLite database, and Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS for the frontend.
reason: The goal is to build a lightweight, responsive edge server on a Raspberry Pi. FastAPI provides a fast API layer and WebSocket support for realtime updates. Vanilla frontend meets the 'no framework' requirement.
impact: Determines the file structure and dependencies.

[CONTEXT LOG]
timestamp: 2026-05-01T11:00:00Z
current_task: Setting up IoT server files based on PROMPT.md
summary: Evaluated requirements and decided on technology stack (FastAPI, SQLite, Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS). Started creating architecture.
active_goals: Create main.py, requirements.txt, run.sh, README.md, and frontend files.
recent_changes: Initialized thought process for project setup.
decisions: FastAPI over Flask for better WebSocket support for realtime data. Premium glassmorphism design for the UI.
assumptions: Python 3 is available on the Raspberry Pi. The .pkg model is either pickable or we can mock it until the user provides the real loading code.
constraints: Lightweight, responsive, no framework on the frontend. Do not write ESP32 code.
risks: The .pkg model format might require specific ML libraries (e.g., scikit-learn, tensorflow), so we'll mock it gracefully.
next_steps: Create MEMORY.md, main.py, requirements.txt, run.sh, documentation, and frontend files.

